---
title: "Active Overlay"
---

Applications can display an overlay on demand regardless of grid state. This is achieved by providing an active overlay which can be one of the provided overlays or be a custom overlay component.

{% gridExampleRunner title="Active Overlay (Component Class)" name="active-overlay-component" exampleHeight=350 /%}

## Display an Active Overlay

To display an overlay on demand set the `activeOverlay` / `activeOverlayParams` grid option. To clear the overlay set `activeOverlay = undefined`.

{% apiDocumentation source="grid-options/properties.json" section="overlays" names=["activeOverlay", "activeOverlayParams"] /%}

{% if isFramework("javascript", "angular") %}
Implement the `IOverlayComp` interface to provide a custom overlay the grid will supply `IOverlayParams` whenever the component is created or refreshed.
{% /if %}
{% if isFramework("angular") %}
{% interfaceDocumentation interfaceName="IOverlayAngularComp" config={"asCode":true } /%}
{% /if %}
{% if isFramework("javascript") %}
{% interfaceDocumentation interfaceName="IOverlayComp" config={"asCode":true } /%}
{% /if %}

{% if isFramework("vue") %}
Any valid Vue component can be used, however the optional `IOverlay` interface exposes lifecycle hooks that receive `IOverlayParams`.
{% /if %}

{% if isFramework("vue") %}
{% interfaceDocumentation interfaceName="IOverlay" config={"asCode":true } /%}
{% /if %}

The example below demonstrates using the grid provided overlays as an active overlay. Note the following:

{% if isFramework("javascript", "angular","react") %}

- activeOverlays take precedence over the provided loading overlay.
- activeOverlay can be displayed no matter what the grid state, i.e showing the no-rows overlay even when there are rows.
- StatusOverlay is registered in the [components](./components/#2-by-name) map and shown by setting `activateOverlay = "statusOverlay"` to the key used.

{% /if %}
{% if isFramework("vue") %}

- activeOverlays take precedence over the provided loading overlay.
- activeOverlay can be displayed no matter what the grid state, i.e showing the no-rows overlay even when there are rows.
- StatusOverlay is registered in the [components](./components/#registering-custom-components) map and shown by setting `activateOverlay = "statusOverlay"` to the key used.

{% /if %}
{% gridExampleRunner title="Active Overlay Switcher" name="active-overlay-switcher" exampleHeight=350 /%}
